When [enable_connection_leak_trace](./agentHelp?key=enable_connection_leak_trace&type=1) option is set to true and java.sql.Connection object is revealed to not be close through leak tracking, DB_CONNECTION_UNCLOSED error is generated.

[enable_connection_fullstack_trace](./agentHelp?key=enable_connection_fullstack_trace&type=1) option is set to true, stack information is added to the error information.

** As the time to track a leak is called by re-defining finalize(), it depends completely on the garbage collection algorithm of JVM. 

---

* Default value: true
* Format: Boolean
* Restart: Not required
* Related options
    * [enable_sql_trace](./agentHelp?key=enable_sql_trace&type=1)
    * [enable_jdbc_wrapper](./agentHelp?key=enable_jdbc_wrapper&type=1)
    * [enable_jdbc_vendor_wrapper](./agentHelp?key=enable_jdbc_vendor_wrapper&type=1)
    * [enable_connection_leak_trace](./agentHelp?key=enable_connection_leak_trace&type=1)
    * [enable_connection_fullstack_trace](./agentHelp?key=enable_connection_fullstack_trace&type=1)
* Supported version: 5.0.0